WEBVTT

1
00:01:14.160 --> 00:01:17.856
[DOREEN LAWRENCE:] 'Stephen
was always creative.

2
00:01:17.880 --> 00:01:21.936
'He had a patient.
careful way about him.

3
00:01:21.960 --> 00:01:25.256
'He used to love sitting with his
father after school and drawing.'

4
00:01:25.280 --> 00:01:27.176
Thank you so much.

5
00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:29.656
'I think he was about
seven when he announced

6
00:01:29.680 --> 00:01:32.376
'that he wanted to be an
architect and he stuck with that.'

7
00:01:32.400 --> 00:01:34.416
I'm sure if he was here.

8
00:01:34.440 --> 00:01:37.296
he'd have a few suggestions
and corrections for you. David.

9
00:01:37.320 --> 00:01:38.800
[THEY CHUCKLE]

10
00:01:42.480 --> 00:01:44.736
Neville. Been waiting long?

11
00:01:44.760 --> 00:01:46.496
13 years...

12
00:01:46.520 --> 00:01:48.536
and counting.

13
00:01:48.560 --> 00:01:51.736
When my son was murdered.

14
00:01:51.760 --> 00:01:55.336
the police thought. "Just
another Black boy stabbed."

15
00:01:55.360 --> 00:01:58.896
But there's no such thing
as "Just another Black boy."

16
00:01:58.920 --> 00:02:03.896
and this building. this centre.
will say that much more loudly

17
00:02:03.920 --> 00:02:05.136
than I can.

18
00:02:05.160 --> 00:02:08.136
And the brilliant young
people who use this space.

19
00:02:08.160 --> 00:02:11.136
they will be Stephen's
living legacy.

20
00:02:11.160 --> 00:02:13.200
[APPLAUSE]

21
00:02:13.540 --> 00:02:16.658
<i><font color="#ff80c0">Provided By M_I_S
www.opensubtitles.org</font></i>

22
00:02:19.640 --> 00:02:23.616
My son's killers were
identified 13 years ago.

23
00:02:23.640 --> 00:02:26.176
within hours of his murder.

24
00:02:26.200 --> 00:02:29.296
Since then. there's been
three investigations.

25
00:02:29.320 --> 00:02:32.376
the law of double
jeopardy was changed

26
00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:33.936
so that murderers
could be retried.

27
00:02:33.960 --> 00:02:37.616
and still. we're sitting
here with no justice.

28
00:02:37.640 --> 00:02:40.696
I understand your
frustration. Mr Lawrence.

29
00:02:40.720 --> 00:02:42.776
but after reviewing
the evidence.

30
00:02:42.800 --> 00:02:45.776
the CPS did not feel there was a
realistic prospect of conviction.

31
00:02:45.800 --> 00:02:49.456
It has been two years since the
last investigation concluded

32
00:02:49.480 --> 00:02:51.456
and we still haven't
seen any evidence.

33
00:02:51.480 --> 00:02:55.456
We have no way of appraising
whether the CPS was justified.

34
00:02:55.480 --> 00:02:58.136
I can assure you it was... No.

35
00:02:58.160 --> 00:03:02.056
No. You can't
"assure" me. because

36
00:03:02.080 --> 00:03:04.776
you're telling me that
there's nothing you can do

37
00:03:04.800 --> 00:03:06.896
and I don't accept that.

38
00:03:06.920 --> 00:03:08.976
I think the only way
forward is to go to court.

39
00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:12.176
seek a judicial review
of this decision.

40
00:03:12.200 --> 00:03:14.816
Mr Lawrence. what I can do

41
00:03:14.840 --> 00:03:17.320
is arrange a review
of your son's case.

42
00:03:20.520 --> 00:03:23.176
Who will be doing this review?

43
00:03:23.200 --> 00:03:26.616
Which one of you is the
investigating officer?

44
00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:28.560
'Morning.'

45
00:03:30.960 --> 00:03:33.656
It's been cleared out. All we've
got to do is hand over these

46
00:03:33.680 --> 00:03:35.536
to the developer

47
00:03:35.560 --> 00:03:37.576
who's 20 minutes late.

48
00:03:37.600 --> 00:03:40.016
Used to be my nick. Yeah?

49
00:03:40.040 --> 00:03:42.056
Well. it's no longer
fit for purpose

50
00:03:42.080 --> 00:03:44.120
in the modern Metropolitan
Police Service.

51
00:04:01.040 --> 00:04:04.576
We're surplus to requirements.
Shaun. like this old dump.

52
00:04:04.600 --> 00:04:08.336
Except when they've finished
here. two-bed flat. half a mil.

53
00:04:08.360 --> 00:04:11.440
This place was supposed to be
empty. What IS all this stuff?

54
00:04:18.480 --> 00:04:20.880
These are case files.

55
00:04:22.080 --> 00:04:25.680
Looks like all police property
has been properly disposed of (!)

56
00:04:29.200 --> 00:04:31.496
Oh. a patrol car.

57
00:04:31.520 --> 00:04:33.040
Easily missed (!)

58
00:04:34.640 --> 00:04:36.816
[CAR HORN] The developer.

59
00:04:36.840 --> 00:04:38.880
Better tell him we're not ready.

60
00:04:45.400 --> 00:04:47.440
SIGHS

61
00:05:25.160 --> 00:05:27.200
[SHAUN: ] Sorted.

62
00:05:32.360 --> 00:05:34.776
Records Management
will be thrilled.

63
00:05:34.800 --> 00:05:36.840
What the hell is
Operation Fishpool?

64
00:05:38.680 --> 00:05:40.536
This is all one case.

65
00:05:40.560 --> 00:05:42.600
Can't be.

66
00:05:52.920 --> 00:05:54.960
[SIGHS]

67
00:05:59.400 --> 00:06:01.920
Oh. Mm.

68
00:06:05.240 --> 00:06:08.040
[FOOTBALL COMMENTARY ON RADIO]

69
00:06:14.440 --> 00:06:17.616
Here you go. lovey.
Thanks. love.

70
00:06:17.640 --> 00:06:19.176
What are you up to?

71
00:06:19.200 --> 00:06:22.496
Just tidying up some
old files from Deptford.

72
00:06:22.520 --> 00:06:24.176
Just some old files?

73
00:06:24.200 --> 00:06:26.360
I know who that is.

74
00:06:27.400 --> 00:06:29.960
[CLEARS THROAT] Well

75
00:06:31.200 --> 00:06:35.416
they were just left
there. gathering dust.

76
00:06:35.440 --> 00:06:38.216
Not right. is it? Case
like this needs solving.

77
00:06:38.240 --> 00:06:40.040
Mm.

78
00:06:54.960 --> 00:06:56.856
[NEWS REPORTER:] 'One
officer who stood out.

79
00:06:56.880 --> 00:06:58.976
'and heavily criticised
by Macpherson.

80
00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:01.416
'was Detective
Sergeant John Davidson.

81
00:07:01.440 --> 00:07:04.696
'He had been responsible for
handling vulnerable witnesses

82
00:07:04.720 --> 00:07:07.136
'and arresting and interviewing
some of the suspects.

83
00:07:07.160 --> 00:07:10.056
'So you're telling
me that key detective

84
00:07:10.080 --> 00:07:13.216
'in the first Lawrence investigation
was corrupt. and in the pocket

85
00:07:13.240 --> 00:07:15.416
'of Clifford Norris. father
of one of the suspects?'

86
00:07:15.440 --> 00:07:17.976
'From my conversation that I had
with John Davidson on that day.

87
00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:21.696
'I would say that John Davidson was
receiving cash from Clifford Norris.

88
00:07:21.720 --> 00:07:24.096
'By his expression that
he was using it as a...

89
00:07:24.120 --> 00:07:26.336
'He was "getting a
little earner" out of it.

90
00:07:26.360 --> 00:07:28.136
'It was "a good little earner".

91
00:07:28.160 --> 00:07:31.240
'Yes. and that. in my mind.
was corrupt practices.'

92
00:07:33.960 --> 00:07:35.376
[HE SIGHS]

93
00:07:35.400 --> 00:07:39.376
Neil Putnam. Ex-detective for
the South-East Crime Squad.

94
00:07:39.400 --> 00:07:42.296
Became a supergrass after getting
arrested for corruption himself.

95
00:07:42.320 --> 00:07:44.736
Why now? If he knew what
was going on all along.

96
00:07:44.760 --> 00:07:48.216
why didn't he speak up
earlier? He says he did.

97
00:07:48.240 --> 00:07:51.936
Claims he told the officers
who debriefed him in 1998.

98
00:07:51.960 --> 00:07:55.136
The Metropolitan Police
have ceased to amaze me.

99
00:07:55.160 --> 00:07:57.816
It's gonna be broadcast
on Wednesday night.

100
00:07:57.840 --> 00:07:59.656
Oh. We'll need to
respond. then. won't we?

101
00:07:59.680 --> 00:08:01.696
I mean. surely this throws
up new lines of inquiry.

102
00:08:01.720 --> 00:08:04.096
What are the police doing?
I'll ask for an update and...

103
00:08:04.120 --> 00:08:06.576
We need the Independent
Police Complaints Commission

104
00:08:06.600 --> 00:08:09.840
to investigate. We need
to keep up the pressure.

105
00:08:15.480 --> 00:08:17.536
To see Deputy Assistant
Commissioner Dick.

106
00:08:17.560 --> 00:08:19.600
If you could just
sign here. please?

107
00:08:21.920 --> 00:08:23.696
[DETECTOR BEEPING]

108
00:08:23.720 --> 00:08:25.776
I'd like to take on the
Stephen Lawrence murder.

109
00:08:25.800 --> 00:08:27.896
The case has already
been allocated.

110
00:08:27.920 --> 00:08:31.816
With all due respect. Ma'am.
the senior investigating officer

111
00:08:31.840 --> 00:08:34.136
is catching cannabis
farmers in Newham.

112
00:08:34.160 --> 00:08:35.536
As far as I can see.

113
00:08:35.560 --> 00:08:38.216
young Stephen's been gathering
dust for the last three years.

114
00:08:38.240 --> 00:08:40.736
No-one seems to want to
touch it with a barge pole.

115
00:08:40.760 --> 00:08:42.536
But you do.

116
00:08:42.560 --> 00:08:44.616
I've been through
the files. Ma'am.

117
00:08:44.640 --> 00:08:47.616
It's a straightforward crime that
I think we should be able to solve

118
00:08:47.640 --> 00:08:49.656
with a bit of
common-sense coppering.

119
00:08:49.680 --> 00:08:51.720
"Common-sense coppering."

120
00:08:53.160 --> 00:08:54.840
Yes. Ma'am.

121
00:08:56.640 --> 00:08:59.416
Right. well. I'll give
it some consideration.

122
00:08:59.440 --> 00:09:01.360
Thank you. DCI Driscoll.

123
00:09:12.560 --> 00:09:14.296
The brass have asked us

124
00:09:14.320 --> 00:09:16.856
to reinvestigate the
murder of Stephen Lawrence.

125
00:09:16.880 --> 00:09:19.216
The Deputy Assistant
Commissioner was quite specific

126
00:09:19.240 --> 00:09:21.016
about this being a review.

127
00:09:21.040 --> 00:09:23.136
I thought we were moving
to proactive stuff.

128
00:09:23.160 --> 00:09:26.136
Change of plan. This'll be our
priority for the foreseeable.

129
00:09:26.160 --> 00:09:28.776
Seriously. hasn't this case
been investigated to death?

130
00:09:28.800 --> 00:09:32.576
You're not wrong there. Tony. This
murder has had three investigations.

131
00:09:32.600 --> 00:09:34.616
six senior
investigating officers.

132
00:09:34.640 --> 00:09:36.336
It's even had a public inquiry.

133
00:09:36.360 --> 00:09:39.496
and yet. no-one has been held to
account for young Stephen's murder.

134
00:09:39.520 --> 00:09:43.416
which means we. the Met.
failed to do our job.

135
00:09:43.440 --> 00:09:46.096
and failed in our duty
to the Lawrence family.

136
00:09:46.120 --> 00:09:49.976
It is our privilege to be
able to put that right.

137
00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:52.736
This is not a whodunnit.
We know "whodunnit".

138
00:09:52.760 --> 00:09:55.856
Norris. Dobson. Knight
and the Acourt double act

139
00:09:55.880 --> 00:10:00.016
were all named by numerous people
within hours of the murder.

140
00:10:00.040 --> 00:10:03.696
What IS a mystery is why. when
there were clear grounds for arrest.

141
00:10:03.720 --> 00:10:07.976
the senior detectives at the time
waited two weeks to pick 'em up.

142
00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:10.296
Two weeks! When we
were in the '90s.

143
00:10:10.320 --> 00:10:12.536
we'd arrest people first.
ask questions later.

144
00:10:12.560 --> 00:10:15.696
We'd arrest just for fun.
They cocked up. badly.

145
00:10:15.720 --> 00:10:17.536
We won't be marking
anyone else's homework.

146
00:10:17.560 --> 00:10:19.096
We'll start from
scratch on the basis

147
00:10:19.120 --> 00:10:21.096
we're more than a match
for a gang of racist thugs.

148
00:10:21.120 --> 00:10:24.376
So. we're gonna need
witnesses. That's you. Birdy.

149
00:10:24.400 --> 00:10:27.776
Tricky. you'll be sorting
all the case files.

150
00:10:27.800 --> 00:10:29.976
The clothes of both
Stephen and the suspects.

151
00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:32.776
we need Forensics to
look at them again.

152
00:10:32.800 --> 00:10:37.216
We're gonna leave no stone
unturned. no stone unanalysed.

153
00:10:37.240 --> 00:10:39.816
no stone uncarefully
noted and filed.

154
00:10:39.840 --> 00:10:42.656
It's gonna be a slog. so if you
don't wanna be here. let me know.

155
00:10:42.680 --> 00:10:44.416
I'll help you get a transfer.

156
00:10:44.440 --> 00:10:47.136
Cos if you don't
wanna be here. well

157
00:10:47.160 --> 00:10:49.736
it's gonna be a nightmare.

158
00:10:49.760 --> 00:10:51.456
Right. any questions?

159
00:10:51.480 --> 00:10:54.696
No. guv. No? Good.
Right. let's get to work.

160
00:10:54.720 --> 00:10:58.640
DI Shaun Keep will be the IO.
He'll be allocating tasks.

161
00:11:12.480 --> 00:11:13.680
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

162
00:11:18.920 --> 00:11:20.856
Guv. I'm out.

163
00:11:20.880 --> 00:11:23.336
I'm just a copper at
the end of the day.

164
00:11:23.360 --> 00:11:25.440
This is a bit. you know. too...

165
00:11:27.600 --> 00:11:30.136
You know what I
mean. No offence.

166
00:11:30.160 --> 00:11:32.496
None taken. Tony. mate.

167
00:11:32.520 --> 00:11:34.960
I appreciate you being
straight with me.

168
00:11:42.360 --> 00:11:44.520
[SIGHS]

169
00:11:50.480 --> 00:11:52.416
Well Hall Road. Eltham.

170
00:11:52.440 --> 00:11:56.016
This is Ground Zero. where
the murder took place.

171
00:11:56.040 --> 00:11:59.456
From now on. this
happened today.

172
00:11:59.480 --> 00:12:02.576
You've just arrived
at the crime scene.

173
00:12:02.600 --> 00:12:05.136
April 22nd. 1993.

174
00:12:05.160 --> 00:12:08.496
Stephen and his friend Duwayne
Brooks are waiting for a bus.

175
00:12:08.520 --> 00:12:10.536
Witnesses say they
were happy. relaxed.

176
00:12:10.560 --> 00:12:12.656
talking about recent
Arsenal signings.

177
00:12:12.680 --> 00:12:15.536
After a few minutes.
the bus hasn't arrived.

178
00:12:15.560 --> 00:12:17.920
so they head back down
towards the roundabout.

179
00:12:22.840 --> 00:12:25.496
From there. they'd be able to see
a bus coming in either direction.

180
00:12:25.520 --> 00:12:28.336
and they could have legged
it to whichever came first.

181
00:12:28.360 --> 00:12:30.856
Keep going. Shaun.

182
00:12:30.880 --> 00:12:32.896
Yes. stop there.

183
00:12:32.920 --> 00:12:36.936
So Stephen was about
there. where Shaun is now.

184
00:12:36.960 --> 00:12:38.680
Duwayne was here. a bit behind.

185
00:12:39.880 --> 00:12:41.296
Duwayne sees another 286.

186
00:12:41.320 --> 00:12:43.936
Then he hears someone
shout racist abuse.

187
00:12:43.960 --> 00:12:45.976
He turns and sees the
first of the white boys

188
00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:48.016
running across the
road towards him.

189
00:12:48.040 --> 00:12:50.936
Duwayne sees them converge
on Stephen. then legs it.

190
00:12:50.960 --> 00:12:52.296
and shouts for Stephen to run.

191
00:12:52.320 --> 00:12:55.856
Witnesses say Stephen was
set upon by five or six men.

192
00:12:55.880 --> 00:12:59.296
They bundled on top of him.
Stephen is stabbed twice.

193
00:12:59.320 --> 00:13:02.536
The knife. or knives. went
five inches into his body.

194
00:13:02.560 --> 00:13:04.296
It was a brief attack. a blur.

195
00:13:04.320 --> 00:13:09.480
When Duwayne looks back. he sees
the gang fleeing up Dickson Road.

196
00:13:14.160 --> 00:13:17.136
Stephen is running towards him.

197
00:13:17.160 --> 00:13:20.256
He runs past the stop. trying
to catch up with Duwayne.

198
00:13:20.280 --> 00:13:22.456
Duwayne's telling him to run.

199
00:13:22.480 --> 00:13:25.440
He's worried the gang are gonna
double back and trap them.

200
00:13:30.320 --> 00:13:33.056
Stephen calls out to his
friend. "What's wrong with me?"

201
00:13:33.080 --> 00:13:36.336
He managed to make it 130 yards
from the site of the attack.

202
00:13:36.360 --> 00:13:39.216
Incredible. considering
the stab wounds

203
00:13:39.240 --> 00:13:42.936
had severed auxiliary arteries
and penetrated his right lung.

204
00:13:42.960 --> 00:13:44.576
He collapses heavily
on the ground here.

205
00:13:44.600 --> 00:13:46.656
and is unresponsive
within seconds.

206
00:13:46.680 --> 00:13:49.216
By now. it's about 10:43.

207
00:13:49.240 --> 00:13:51.696
At 11:05. on arrival
at Brook General.

208
00:13:51.720 --> 00:13:53.720
Stephen Lawrence
was already dead.

