225
00:15:03.440 --> 00:15:07.536
I feel some peace when
I'm in Jamaica. you know?

226
00:15:07.560 --> 00:15:09.720
But England?

227
00:15:10.920 --> 00:15:12.936
Every time I come back here.

228
00:15:12.960 --> 00:15:16.416
I just start to feel so
angry all over again.

229
00:15:16.440 --> 00:15:18.256
Yeah.

230
00:15:18.280 --> 00:15:20.320
You have a lot to
be angry about.

231
00:15:21.760 --> 00:15:24.216
I know.

232
00:15:24.240 --> 00:15:26.656
But it's not a nice way to feel.

233
00:15:26.680 --> 00:15:28.616
We keep you in our
prayers. Neville.

234
00:15:28.640 --> 00:15:31.096
I know. and I'm... I'm grateful.

235
00:15:31.120 --> 00:15:35.536
but it's hard to pray when
your heart is full of hate.

236
00:15:35.560 --> 00:15:39.440
That's the thing that holds
me back from being baptised.

237
00:15:41.360 --> 00:15:44.200
All He asks is that
you open your heart.

238
00:15:45.600 --> 00:15:47.416
He'll do the rest.

239
00:15:47.440 --> 00:15:50.816
You know

240
00:15:50.840 --> 00:15:55.280
after Stephen died. after
the first trial collapsed

241
00:15:57.240 --> 00:16:01.536
a man came to see
me and he said that

242
00:16:01.560 --> 00:16:03.576
he could take the burden.

243
00:16:03.600 --> 00:16:06.816
told me that if the police
couldn't give me justice.

244
00:16:06.840 --> 00:16:09.096
then he could.

245
00:16:09.120 --> 00:16:11.696
Outside the law.

246
00:16:11.720 --> 00:16:14.176
You understand what I'm
talking about. yeah?

247
00:16:14.200 --> 00:16:16.816
An eye for an eye.

248
00:16:16.840 --> 00:16:18.600
But Neville...

249
00:16:20.760 --> 00:16:26.040
I told him no. because I knew
I didn't want to be like them.

250
00:16:29.280 --> 00:16:32.920
I didn't want hate
to consume me.

251
00:16:35.520 --> 00:16:38.080
But when the Lord tells us.
"Turn the other cheek"...

252
00:16:39.720 --> 00:16:41.856
I...

253
00:16:41.880 --> 00:16:44.736
I don't know where
to begin with that.

254
00:16:44.760 --> 00:16:46.960
What does it mean to
"turn the other cheek"

255
00:16:50.360 --> 00:16:52.920
when your son has been murdered?

256
00:16:56.240 --> 00:16:58.280
What does anything
mean after that?

257
00:17:00.160 --> 00:17:02.056
Clive. All right. mate?

258
00:17:02.080 --> 00:17:05.696
All right. Bill? Jammy win
against Liverpool. that.

259
00:17:05.720 --> 00:17:09.496
Jammy? Nothing jammy about
it. mate. Pure artistry.

260
00:17:09.520 --> 00:17:12.176
Listen. commiserations getting
that case dumped on you.

261
00:17:12.200 --> 00:17:15.216
Waste of time and
money. I don't follow.

262
00:17:15.240 --> 00:17:17.376
Saint Stephen Lawrence.

263
00:17:17.400 --> 00:17:19.440
I mean. what makes
him so special. eh?

264
00:17:20.480 --> 00:17:22.536
It's embarrassing how we
kowtow to that family.

265
00:17:22.560 --> 00:17:24.656
just for them to slag us
off at every opportunity.

266
00:17:24.680 --> 00:17:28.576
Thing is. we didn't
finish the job. did we?

267
00:17:28.600 --> 00:17:31.920
I mean. I'd be slagging us
off if I was in their shoes.

268
00:17:50.680 --> 00:17:53.216
Case record's a mess. guv.

269
00:17:53.240 --> 00:17:55.960
We're missing witness
statements. got blank actions...

270
00:17:58.080 --> 00:18:01.096
Well. if they've made a hash of
it. we're never gonna patch it up.

271
00:18:01.120 --> 00:18:03.536
so start it again
and start it right.

272
00:18:03.560 --> 00:18:05.976
Well. we've got 540
boxes back there.

273
00:18:06.000 --> 00:18:08.016
That's tens of
thousands of documents.

274
00:18:08.040 --> 00:18:10.840
Better get a start on.
then. hadn't you. Tricky?

275
00:18:14.040 --> 00:18:16.296
I'll see what we can do.

276
00:18:16.320 --> 00:18:18.440
Maybe we can stretch
to another indexer.

277
00:18:21.160 --> 00:18:23.576
There's a few potential
witnesses on the estate

278
00:18:23.600 --> 00:18:25.816
we're pretty sure could put
the gang near the scene.

279
00:18:25.840 --> 00:18:29.056
Great. Bring 'em in.
It's complicated.

280
00:18:29.080 --> 00:18:32.056
Basically. they told us
where to go. Keep going.

281
00:18:32.080 --> 00:18:36.696
Well. we've got witness K.
right? He knew the suspects.

282
00:18:36.720 --> 00:18:39.736
He said he visited the Acourts
on the night of the murder.

283
00:18:39.760 --> 00:18:42.776
He saw Neil Acourt and David
Norris in a state of undress.

284
00:18:42.800 --> 00:18:44.856
as if in the process
of cleaning themselves.

285
00:18:44.880 --> 00:18:46.376
Perfect.

286
00:18:46.400 --> 00:18:48.856
He wasn't interviewed
for another 12 days.

287
00:18:48.880 --> 00:18:52.336
The kid apparently became
fearful of reprisals

288
00:18:52.360 --> 00:18:54.936
and has refused to
co-operate ever since.

289
00:18:54.960 --> 00:18:57.776
And then. well. there's a pattern.
You know. he's a decent witness.

290
00:18:57.800 --> 00:19:00.096
delays in following 'im
up. and changes of heart.

291
00:19:00.120 --> 00:19:02.376
We're talking about
kids. for Christ sakes.

292
00:19:02.400 --> 00:19:04.416
First priority should be
making them feel safe.

293
00:19:04.440 --> 00:19:07.576
Well. as it stands.
they don't love us. guv.

294
00:19:07.600 --> 00:19:10.256
What about Stephen's
friend. Duwayne Brooks?

295
00:19:10.280 --> 00:19:12.416
Now. he really. really
doesn't love us.

296
00:19:12.440 --> 00:19:14.616
He wasn't handled well
in the past either.

297
00:19:14.640 --> 00:19:17.696
and now he's wary of us. We're
gonna have to reassure him.

298
00:19:17.720 --> 00:19:19.856
Not only is he a witness.
he's the second victim.

299
00:19:19.880 --> 00:19:21.920
He's vital. Got it.

300
00:19:23.480 --> 00:19:26.256
What about Mr and Mrs Lawrence?
Are we gonna meet with them?

301
00:19:26.280 --> 00:19:28.216
No. they've been through enough.

302
00:19:28.240 --> 00:19:31.600
I'm not going near them till
I've actually got some good news.

303
00:19:36.920 --> 00:19:39.400
Thank you so much for
coming in. Mrs Lawrence.

304
00:19:41.080 --> 00:19:43.056
I want to acknowledge
at the outset

305
00:19:43.080 --> 00:19:45.760
the great injustice
your family has endured.

306
00:19:47.920 --> 00:19:50.576
I think it's fair to
say your son's case.

307
00:19:50.600 --> 00:19:53.056
and the hard lessons learned
from its many failures.

308
00:19:53.080 --> 00:19:57.176
are part of the IPCC's
organisational DNA.

309
00:19:57.200 --> 00:19:59.016
I think it would be helpful

310
00:19:59.040 --> 00:20:02.200
if we could clarify the terms of
reference of your investigation.

311
00:20:04.400 --> 00:20:06.736
Yes. of course.

312
00:20:06.760 --> 00:20:08.856
The key question
we aim to answer

313
00:20:08.880 --> 00:20:11.376
is whether ex-Detective
Sergeant John Davidson

314
00:20:11.400 --> 00:20:14.096
had a corrupt relationship
with Clifford Norris.

315
00:20:14.120 --> 00:20:16.296
the father of one
of the suspects.

316
00:20:16.320 --> 00:20:19.896
We had concerns about the initial
investigation from the start.

317
00:20:19.920 --> 00:20:21.456
Rest assured.

318
00:20:21.480 --> 00:20:24.856
we will be going through Davidson's
actions with a fine-tooth comb.

319
00:20:24.880 --> 00:20:30.536
My point is. I don't believe the
problem was one corrupt detective.

320
00:20:30.560 --> 00:20:34.016
My fear for a long time is that
this has been an anti-investigation.

321
00:20:34.040 --> 00:20:37.080
designed to cover up the truth.

322
00:20:47.800 --> 00:20:49.896
[READS:] "Since the
suspects were not arrested"

323
00:20:49.920 --> 00:20:52.056
"until at least two
weeks after the event.

324
00:20:52.080 --> 00:20:54.176
"I believe that looking at
their clothes for fibres"

325
00:20:54.200 --> 00:20:56.656
"that could have come from
Stephen Lawrence's clothing"

326
00:20:56.680 --> 00:20:58.720
"is not worthwhile at all."

327
00:21:11.000 --> 00:21:13.696
[MAN ON VIDEO:] 'If I was gonna kill
myself. do you know what I'd do?

328
00:21:13.720 --> 00:21:16.336
'I'd go and kill every
Black cunt. every Paki.

329
00:21:16.360 --> 00:21:18.536
'every copper. every mug...'

330
00:21:18.560 --> 00:21:20.800
Morning.

331
00:21:22.320 --> 00:21:25.896
Surveillance tapes from '94.
Just got 'em from the archives.

332
00:21:25.920 --> 00:21:29.336
'Skin the Black cunt alive. mate.
Torture him. set him alight.

333
00:21:29.360 --> 00:21:33.136
'I'd blow the two legs and arms off
and say. "Go on. swim home now!" '

334
00:21:33.160 --> 00:21:34.656
[SIGHS]

335
00:21:34.680 --> 00:21:37.760
And this is from the
surveillance team.

336
00:21:39.480 --> 00:21:41.520
The whole gang at a
christening a week ago.

337
00:21:47.080 --> 00:21:49.896
Look at them. Not a
care in the world.

338
00:21:49.920 --> 00:21:51.976
How did they not
nail these bastards?

339
00:21:52.000 --> 00:21:55.616
I'll give you one reason. They
didn't check their clothes fully.

340
00:21:55.640 --> 00:21:57.776
What do you mean?
Forensic Science Service.

341
00:21:57.800 --> 00:22:01.096
They didn't look for fibres from
Stephen on the suspects' clothing.

342
00:22:01.120 --> 00:22:03.696
Well. yeah. but it
was a brief attack.

343
00:22:03.720 --> 00:22:08.976
Yeah. it says... here. "Brief
attack. out in the open."

344
00:22:09.000 --> 00:22:13.296
"chances of forensic
exchange vanishingly small."

345
00:22:13.320 --> 00:22:15.976
Who said it was brief?
First investigation did.

346
00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:18.976
It was in the original lab
request. "Brief attack".

347
00:22:19.000 --> 00:22:21.096
These phrases. someone
uses them once.

348
00:22:21.120 --> 00:22:23.136
and they get repeated
as if they're gospel.

349
00:22:23.160 --> 00:22:26.016
What does "brief" even mean?
What. five seconds. five minutes?

350
00:22:26.040 --> 00:22:27.576
It's hardly precise. is it?

351
00:22:27.600 --> 00:22:30.056
Right. and then there's
the 15-day delay

352
00:22:30.080 --> 00:22:32.936
before the suspects'
clothing was seized.

353
00:22:32.960 --> 00:22:36.336
The forensic people reckoned any
traces would have been lost by then.

354
00:22:36.360 --> 00:22:38.176
If they washed them.
but that's a big if.

355
00:22:38.200 --> 00:22:40.776
The clothes might have just been
sat at the back of a wardrobe.

356
00:22:40.800 --> 00:22:43.096
They say there's
no point checking.

357
00:22:43.120 --> 00:22:45.736
I tell you. if I had a quid for
every time a scientist has told me

358
00:22:45.760 --> 00:22:48.016
there's no point doing
something I asked them to do.

359
00:22:48.040 --> 00:22:50.120
I'd be able to buy Fulham
a new centre forward.

360
00:22:51.720 --> 00:22:55.816
I mean. a small chance
isn't no chance. is it?

361
00:22:55.840 --> 00:22:58.000
A small chance is a chance.

362
00:23:02.960 --> 00:23:05.696
We're gonna need
fresh eyes on this.

363
00:23:05.720 --> 00:23:07.816
This case has had half
a dozen inquiries.

364
00:23:07.840 --> 00:23:09.456
No-one's ever raised concerns

365
00:23:09.480 --> 00:23:11.936
about the conduct of the
Forensic Science Service.

366
00:23:11.960 --> 00:23:14.256
Well. there's your trouble.

367
00:23:14.280 --> 00:23:16.656
Look. in '93. the SIO
said. "Do everything."

368
00:23:16.680 --> 00:23:18.736
Then the FSS bods
come back and say.

369
00:23:18.760 --> 00:23:21.776
"No point doing this. no chance
with that. vanishingly small."

370
00:23:21.800 --> 00:23:23.936
and the SIO says. "OK.
forget it. You know best."

371
00:23:23.960 --> 00:23:26.296
It was a brief attack.
out in the open.

372
00:23:26.320 --> 00:23:28.336
The most likely reason
for them finding nothing

373
00:23:28.360 --> 00:23:29.736
is there was nothing to find.

374
00:23:29.760 --> 00:23:31.776
They didn't even examine
the suspects' clothing

375
00:23:31.800 --> 00:23:33.016
for traces from Stephen.

376
00:23:33.040 --> 00:23:35.336
You can't find what
you're not looking for.

377
00:23:35.360 --> 00:23:38.696
What are you actually proposing.
Clive? I wanna go private.

378
00:23:38.720 --> 00:23:40.976
The FSS didn't do what
they were asked last time.

379
00:23:41.000 --> 00:23:43.209
They'll be defensive if they
have to go over it again.

380
00:23:46.440 --> 00:23:50.056
Hello. I'm Angela
Gallop. strategic lead.

381
00:23:50.080 --> 00:23:52.216
And this is Ed Jarman... Hi.

382
00:23:52.240 --> 00:23:54.376
One of our forensic
scientists. Hello.

383
00:23:54.400 --> 00:23:56.560
DCI Clive Driscoll.
DI Shaun King.

384
00:23:59.120 --> 00:24:01.896
First things first. I want
you to test for everything.

385
00:24:01.920 --> 00:24:03.696
blood. hair. fibres.

386
00:24:03.720 --> 00:24:06.256
If there's a test or a process
out there. I want it done.

387
00:24:06.280 --> 00:24:09.736
Now. you might know full well. "No
point testing for this or that."

388
00:24:09.760 --> 00:24:11.776
but I'm gonna ask
you to do it anyway.

389
00:24:11.800 --> 00:24:14.856
There have been huge advances in
micro-spectroscopy since the '90s.

390
00:24:14.880 --> 00:24:17.536
That's great. er. but
before we get into that.

391
00:24:17.560 --> 00:24:19.696
I'd be grateful if you
could sign this memorandum

392
00:24:19.720 --> 00:24:22.256
confirming that the forensic
review will be police-led.

393
00:24:22.280 --> 00:24:24.456
I don't think I've ever had
to sign one of these before.

394
00:24:24.480 --> 00:24:26.496
No. it's something
I came up with.

395
00:24:26.520 --> 00:24:28.216
I'll be carrying
the can on this one.

396
00:24:28.240 --> 00:24:31.760
We don't wanna repeat the mistakes
of the last forensic investigation.

397
00:24:33.800 --> 00:24:35.360
You were saying about the tests?

398
00:24:36.800 --> 00:24:38.856
Yes. Looking at the FSS reports.

399
00:24:38.880 --> 00:24:41.656
I mean. the obvious omission
is a Phadebas press test.

400
00:24:41.680 --> 00:24:44.656
Sorry. that's an
alpha-amylase test. Saliva.

401
00:24:44.680 --> 00:24:47.576
Yeah. I mean. like I say.
half of what you're doing

402
00:24:47.600 --> 00:24:50.496
will be lost on me. but I
want you to do it anyway.

403
00:24:50.520 --> 00:24:53.496
We do need to bear in mind
that this was a brief attack.

404
00:24:53.520 --> 00:24:55.736
I don't want to overpromise.

405
00:24:55.760 --> 00:24:58.736
But. as we say. every
contact leaves a trace.

406
00:24:58.760 --> 00:25:00.600
Thank you.

407
00:25:01.760 --> 00:25:03.800
Right.

408
00:25:13.840 --> 00:25:15.536
[CLIVE SIGHS]

409
00:25:15.560 --> 00:25:17.856
They weren't excited enough.

410
00:25:17.880 --> 00:25:20.536
Seemed keen to get going to me.

411
00:25:20.560 --> 00:25:23.880
It's that "brief attack"
line. It lowers expectations.

412
00:25:25.480 --> 00:25:29.376
I mean. he was attacked by
five lads. for Christ sakes.

413
00:25:29.400 --> 00:25:31.600
What's brief times five?
It's not brief. is it?

414
00:25:35.600 --> 00:25:38.760
We've just got to bring
it to life for them.

415
00:25:40.280 --> 00:25:44.976
It's a technical reconstruction. so
no need for. er. amateur dramatics.

416
00:25:45.000 --> 00:25:47.656
Shaun here is gonna stand
in for one of the attackers.

417
00:25:47.680 --> 00:25:49.696
You all right with that. Theo?

418
00:25:49.720 --> 00:25:52.080
Yeah. Sure. I...
remember the case.

419
00:25:53.520 --> 00:25:55.976
Well. I don't remember
it. obviously.

420
00:25:56.000 --> 00:25:57.856
I was only a kid.

421
00:25:57.880 --> 00:26:00.576
Yeah. You were. weren't you?

422
00:26:00.600 --> 00:26:02.256
Did I say the wrong thing?

423
00:26:02.280 --> 00:26:05.016
No. it's just that it's
been a long wait. hasn't it?

424
00:26:05.040 --> 00:26:07.080
For them.

425
00:26:10.640 --> 00:26:14.456
Right. well. Stephen's body was
covered in bruises and abrasions

426
00:26:14.480 --> 00:26:16.696
from being kicked and punched.

427
00:26:16.720 --> 00:26:19.696
There were two stab wounds.
both about five inches each.

428
00:26:19.720 --> 00:26:21.776
on the right collarbone
and left shoulder.

429
00:26:21.800 --> 00:26:24.336
We're gonna go through each of
the witness statements in turn.

430
00:26:24.360 --> 00:26:25.896
work out the consistencies.

431
00:26:25.920 --> 00:26:28.160
and see if we can work
out how the injuries fit.

432
00:26:31.760 --> 00:26:34.136
So. you come at him
from this direction.

433
00:26:34.160 --> 00:26:38.376
Stephen's hand turns. and as
they surround him. he goes under.

434
00:26:38.400 --> 00:26:40.656
Yeah. on your right side.

435
00:26:40.680 --> 00:26:42.800
That matches the position
for the entry wound.

436
00:26:44.440 --> 00:26:48.096
Er. witnesses say
a punch was thrown.

437
00:26:48.120 --> 00:26:50.440
a kick that didn't land.

438
00:26:51.480 --> 00:26:54.616
Then Stephen tries
to wriggle free.

439
00:26:54.640 --> 00:26:58.696
This is when the second stab
wound might have been sustained.

440
00:26:58.720 --> 00:27:00.760
No. no. no. overarm.
like you're bowling.

441
00:27:03.720 --> 00:27:05.320
Yeah.

442
00:27:08.080 --> 00:27:10.120
Go.

443
00:27:25.440 --> 00:27:27.440
[THEO EXHALES]

444
00:27:30.480 --> 00:27:32.656
[SIGHS]

445
00:27:32.680 --> 00:27:35.456
Not long enough. You got through
less than half the injuries.

446
00:27:35.480 --> 00:27:39.736
He's got abrasions here. here
and here. on the left side.

447
00:27:39.760 --> 00:27:43.056
Then he's got entry wounds
on the left and the right.

448
00:27:43.080 --> 00:27:46.080
so. somewhere. he's flipped.

449
00:27:47.720 --> 00:27:50.000
There had to be more blows.

450
00:27:56.040 --> 00:27:58.080
Go.

451
00:28:32.640 --> 00:28:35.200
[SHAUN AND THEO PANTING]

452
00:28:40.400 --> 00:28:42.816
That's a result.

453
00:28:42.840 --> 00:28:44.120
Good lad.

454
00:28:52.480 --> 00:28:54.616
Are you all right there. Shaun?

455
00:28:54.640 --> 00:28:56.680
Bit warm?

456
00:28:58.680 --> 00:29:01.336
You OK. Theo?

457
00:29:01.360 --> 00:29:04.200
Yeah. Just. you know.

458
00:29:06.320 --> 00:29:09.880
I just really hope you
nail them. guv. That's all.

459
00:30:05.040 --> 00:30:07.080
That wasn't brief.

460
00:30:08.800 --> 00:30:12.696
In anyone's book.
that is an intense.

461
00:30:12.720 --> 00:30:14.776
relatively prolonged assault.

462
00:30:14.800 --> 00:30:17.640
Our estimate is
25 to 30 seconds.

463
00:30:19.160 --> 00:30:22.256
The first investigation
described it as "a brief attack".

464
00:30:22.280 --> 00:30:24.576
and that's haunted
us ever since.

465
00:30:24.600 --> 00:30:27.480
That phrase has been as good
as an alibi to the murderers.

466
00:30:30.000 --> 00:30:32.500
There must have been a very
large amount of contact. in fact.

467
00:30:33.840 --> 00:30:36.736
And I'm thinking about
the attackers' trousers.

468
00:30:36.760 --> 00:30:40.256
Just looking at the video.
Stephen was on the ground.

469
00:30:40.280 --> 00:30:43.216
They must have had to
kick him to keep him down.

470
00:30:43.240 --> 00:30:45.656
There are so many opportunities
for fibre transfer.

471
00:30:45.680 --> 00:30:48.256
And if there were multiple
blows after the stabbing.

472
00:30:48.280 --> 00:30:50.616
then there's potential for a
lot more droplet dispersal.

473
00:30:50.640 --> 00:30:54.976
And the rips in Stephen's clothing.
that's a potential site for... Mm.

474
00:30:55.000 --> 00:30:58.096
This opens up a lot of
interesting avenues.

475
00:30:58.120 --> 00:31:00.776
but there's one problem.

476
00:31:00.800 --> 00:31:03.296
The Forensic Science Service.

477
00:31:03.320 --> 00:31:05.056
I told them to send
you everything.

478
00:31:05.080 --> 00:31:08.496
Yes. well. they didn't. They
withheld their paperwork

479
00:31:08.520 --> 00:31:10.920
on the grounds that they're
commercially sensitive.

480
00:31:12.080 --> 00:31:16.176
I will give you 48 hours. then
I'm getting a Section 1 warrant

481
00:31:16.200 --> 00:31:18.896
and I'm seizing MY exhibits.

482
00:31:18.920 --> 00:31:20.456
They're civil servants.

483
00:31:20.480 --> 00:31:23.776
You can't get a warrant against
the government. can you?

484
00:31:23.800 --> 00:31:26.176
They're interfering with the
administration of justice.

485
00:31:26.200 --> 00:31:28.416
I tell you. just trying to
make a start on this case

486
00:31:28.440 --> 00:31:30.640
is like pulling teeth.
OK. Leave it with me.

487
00:31:53.240 --> 00:31:55.920
Here you go. Thank you.

488
00:32:21.600 --> 00:32:24.000
Hello...

489
00:32:26.200 --> 00:32:28.360
You're not from
round here. are you?

490
00:32:31.160 --> 00:32:35.096
Red fibres? Must be from
the ambulance blanket.

491
00:32:35.120 --> 00:32:36.257
They're red. aren't they?

492
00:32:36.281 --> 00:32:38.216
Thought of that.

493
00:32:38.240 --> 00:32:41.256
but these are a completely different
colour under magnification.

494
00:32:41.280 --> 00:32:44.696
Almost orange. We keep finding more
of them on Stephen's outer garments.

495
00:32:44.720 --> 00:32:48.936
What about Stephen's polo shirt?
Can you test against that?

496
00:32:48.960 --> 00:32:51.416
The polo shirt was
under two other layers.

497
00:32:51.440 --> 00:32:53.456
'I can't see how the
fibres could transfer.'

498
00:32:53.480 --> 00:32:55.360
If the test can be
done. I want it done.

499
00:33:14.520 --> 00:33:15.816
You were right.

500
00:33:15.840 --> 00:33:18.776
The fibres are microscopically
indistinguishable

501
00:33:18.800 --> 00:33:20.376
from Stephen's polo shirt.

502
00:33:20.400 --> 00:33:24.880
So. back to your question
- how did they get there?

503
00:33:26.240 --> 00:33:32.240
For Stephen's polo shirt to transfer
fibres to the outside of his coat

504
00:33:32.520 --> 00:33:36.096
they must have had
high... "shedability".

505
00:33:36.120 --> 00:33:41.296
Well. I'm not sure
that's a word. but yes.

506
00:33:41.320 --> 00:33:44.376
Remarkably high...
"shedability".

507
00:33:44.400 --> 00:33:46.576
So those fibres could be...

508
00:33:46.600 --> 00:33:49.656
On anything that
touched Stephen's coat.

509
00:33:49.680 --> 00:33:51.960
It certainly helps to know
what we're looking for.

510
00:33:56.920 --> 00:34:00.656
So this is it? This
is your final report?

511
00:34:00.680 --> 00:34:02.256
Yes.

512
00:34:02.280 --> 00:34:04.576
And while we do
not ultimately find

513
00:34:04.600 --> 00:34:07.416
the corruption allegations
presented in the documentary

514
00:34:07.440 --> 00:34:09.096
to be credible.

515
00:34:09.120 --> 00:34:11.736
we do make several
learning recommendations

516
00:34:11.760 --> 00:34:13.656
to the Metropolitan Police.

517
00:34:13.680 --> 00:34:17.416
But you didn't actually
interview Davidson.

518
00:34:17.440 --> 00:34:21.256
As ex-Detective Sergeant Davidson
is no longer a serving officer.

519
00:34:21.280 --> 00:34:24.216
we couldn't compel
him to co-operate.

520
00:34:24.240 --> 00:34:27.656
At any rate. we were unable
to find any documents

521
00:34:27.680 --> 00:34:30.280
to corroborate Mr
Putnam's claims.

522
00:34:31.680 --> 00:34:35.696
This was an investigation into
police corruption and cover-up.

523
00:34:35.720 --> 00:34:39.856
Surely you wouldn't expect officers
to document their own malfeasances.

524
00:34:39.880 --> 00:34:44.080
We found no evidence at
all to suggest corruption.

525
00:34:51.280 --> 00:34:54.576
I know this is not the outcome
you wanted. Mrs Lawrence.

526
00:34:54.600 --> 00:34:57.296
but I am confident that
Putnam was mistaken.

527
00:34:57.320 --> 00:34:59.096
Well. I'm glad you're confident.

528
00:34:59.120 --> 00:35:02.696
Personally. I don't have much
confidence in police officers

529
00:35:02.720 --> 00:35:04.640
investigating police officers.

530
00:35:05.600 --> 00:35:08.856
[SHAUN: ] 19-year-old French au pair
gave a witness statement. but...

531
00:35:08.880 --> 00:35:10.160
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

532
00:35:11.640 --> 00:35:12.817
Angela.

533
00:35:12.841 --> 00:35:16.456
Your theory of
"shedability" was correct.

534
00:35:16.480 --> 00:35:19.096
These were found
on Dobson's jacket

535
00:35:19.120 --> 00:35:22.696
and these on Norris's trousers.

536
00:35:22.720 --> 00:35:26.200
Microscopically indistinguishable
from Stephen's polo shirt.

537
00:35:27.480 --> 00:35:29.496
You realise this is the
first physical evidence

538
00:35:29.520 --> 00:35:31.440
linking any of the
suspects with Stephen?

539
00:35:32.600 --> 00:35:35.160
I think we can say your
hunch has been vindicated.

540
00:35:36.560 --> 00:35:39.416
So... you're telling
me we've got a case?

541
00:35:39.440 --> 00:35:41.640
Yes. I think you do.

542
00:35:49.960 --> 00:35:52.520
I think it's time for us
to speak to the family.

543
00:35:57.480 --> 00:36:00.280
[WEATHER REPORT ON RADIO]

544
00:36:04.320 --> 00:36:07.736
'Looking ahead to tomorrow. and
that band of low pressure lifts...'

545
00:36:07.760 --> 00:36:10.240
Hi. Mum. Hi. Gina.

546
00:36:17.240 --> 00:36:20.536
Were you working late
again last night?

547
00:36:20.560 --> 00:36:22.040
When do you ever relax?

548
00:36:23.320 --> 00:36:25.736
I've got a job to do.

549
00:36:25.760 --> 00:36:29.216
Mum. you need time for
yourself. too. you know?

550
00:36:29.240 --> 00:36:32.136
You should think about putting
yourself out there more.

551
00:36:32.160 --> 00:36:34.056
I AM out there and busy.

552
00:36:34.080 --> 00:36:37.136
I am! I've got the centre.
I've got fundraising

553
00:36:37.160 --> 00:36:38.576
and bursary applications...

554
00:36:38.600 --> 00:36:43.096
Mum. that's not what I mean.
I'm talking about... you know.

555
00:36:43.120 --> 00:36:46.400
Well. it's not like
I'm hiding away. is it?

556
00:36:47.880 --> 00:36:50.096
I would like to
have some company.

557
00:36:50.120 --> 00:36:53.680
but men don't seems to
know how to approach me.

558
00:37:00.440 --> 00:37:04.736
Mr Lawrence. Thank you so
much for making the time. sir.

559
00:37:04.760 --> 00:37:07.280
All right. You're just in time.

560
00:37:08.400 --> 00:37:10.416
I'm flying back to
Jamaica tomorrow.

561
00:37:10.440 --> 00:37:12.920
and I have a school
visit this afternoon.

562
00:37:16.280 --> 00:37:19.256
I understand that
you've been asked

563
00:37:19.280 --> 00:37:23.016
to carry out some kind of
review of my son's case.

564
00:37:23.040 --> 00:37:25.416
Well. given the
progress we've made.

565
00:37:25.440 --> 00:37:28.016
it's now a full reinvestigation.

566
00:37:28.040 --> 00:37:31.696
And I wasn't asked. I
volunteered. as it happens.

567
00:37:31.720 --> 00:37:33.616
Progress? Yes.

568
00:37:33.640 --> 00:37:35.696
I have to ask you to
keep this to yourself.

569
00:37:35.720 --> 00:37:39.256
but we've found new evidence
implicating several of the suspects.

570
00:37:39.280 --> 00:37:41.616
What kind of evidence?

571
00:37:41.640 --> 00:37:45.256
Forensic evidence. Fibres
from Stephen's clothing

572
00:37:45.280 --> 00:37:47.760
have been found on the
suspects' clothing.

573
00:37:51.040 --> 00:37:52.440
Right.

574
00:37:54.240 --> 00:37:55.600
So...

575
00:37:58.840 --> 00:38:01.736
Sorry. I... I wasn't
expecting this.

576
00:38:01.760 --> 00:38:03.496
The forensic review is ongoing.

577
00:38:03.520 --> 00:38:05.576
Look. I don't want you
to get your hopes up.

578
00:38:05.600 --> 00:38:08.696
but this is the first time we've
had actual physical evidence

579
00:38:08.720 --> 00:38:11.160
linking the suspects
to your son.

580
00:38:12.560 --> 00:38:17.056
And... And these suspects.
you mean the same boys...?

581
00:38:17.080 --> 00:38:19.120
Yes. Four members
of the Acourt gang.

582
00:38:23.600 --> 00:38:28.000
Good. That's... good news.

583
00:38:31.960 --> 00:38:35.536
Sorry. I'm not really
used to good news.

584
00:38:35.560 --> 00:38:37.520
Well. you've waited a long time.

585
00:38:38.600 --> 00:38:40.776
Too long.

586
00:38:40.800 --> 00:38:42.496
I can only apologise for that.

587
00:38:42.520 --> 00:38:44.976
You say you volunteered
to take on my son's case?

588
00:38:45.000 --> 00:38:48.400
I did. sir. yes.
Why you do that?

589
00:38:50.800 --> 00:38:53.056
I think a young lad should
be able to catch the bus home

590
00:38:53.080 --> 00:38:54.816
without being killed.

591
00:38:54.840 --> 00:38:58.616
I mean. if we can't solve
a murder like Stephen's.

592
00:38:58.640 --> 00:39:00.680
what's the point of us?

593
00:39:03.920 --> 00:39:05.640
Just do your best. officer.

594
00:39:07.400 --> 00:39:09.920
That's all we ever
ask. you know. Just

595
00:39:12.320 --> 00:39:15.880
do your best. for Stephen.

596
00:39:44.880 --> 00:39:46.936
[DOREEN:] 'There's racism
in every walk of life.

597
00:39:46.960 --> 00:39:50.856
'Look. we have a candidate for
London Mayor. Boris Johnson.

598
00:39:50.880 --> 00:39:54.496
'who talks about "piccaninnies
with watermelon smiles".

599
00:39:54.520 --> 00:39:57.576
'That's not banter.
that's racism.'

600
00:39:57.600 --> 00:39:59.296
[RADIO:] 'I think
Boris is right.

601
00:39:59.320 --> 00:40:03.856
'This isn't about justice any more.
it's politically-correct hysteria.

602
00:40:03.880 --> 00:40:06.256
'We have Jean on the line.'

603
00:40:06.280 --> 00:40:08.976
'I don't know why people
give her a platform.

604
00:40:09.000 --> 00:40:12.816
'I mean. it was. what.
15 years ago. almost?

605
00:40:12.840 --> 00:40:14.680
'Can't we move on?'

606
00:40:24.440 --> 00:40:26.376
So what do you
think this is about?

607
00:40:26.400 --> 00:40:28.976
Well. they could be about to
tell us it's the end of the road.

608
00:40:29.000 --> 00:40:31.416
What do you mean? That they'll
close the investigation?

609
00:40:31.440 --> 00:40:34.240
Well. we won't accept
that. No. of course not.

610
00:40:37.120 --> 00:40:39.936
Detective Chief
Inspector Clive Driscoll

611
00:40:39.960 --> 00:40:42.696
has been leading a review
of your son's case.

612
00:40:42.720 --> 00:40:46.176
and I am going to ask
him to provide an update.

613
00:40:46.200 --> 00:40:49.096
This is in
confidence. of course.

614
00:40:49.120 --> 00:40:51.176
Erm. thank you.

615
00:40:51.200 --> 00:40:53.576
First of all. we
reviewed the forensics.

616
00:40:53.600 --> 00:40:56.216
and we believe we've
found new evidence

617
00:40:56.240 --> 00:40:58.776
linking Stephen with
several suspects.

618
00:40:58.800 --> 00:41:00.296
Er...

619
00:41:00.320 --> 00:41:04.080
Now. obviously. this is not
a real person. obviously.

620
00:41:05.680 --> 00:41:08.176
Sorry. Yeah. obv... obviously.

621
00:41:08.200 --> 00:41:14.200
What this is is a distribution of
fibres from Stephen's clothing.

622
00:41:14.360 --> 00:41:16.976
Some of the red fibres
from his T-shirt

623
00:41:17.000 --> 00:41:20.600
have been found on the clothes
of some of the suspects.

624
00:41:22.440 --> 00:41:25.576
And they are definitely
from his... Red polo top.

625
00:41:25.600 --> 00:41:27.480
That's the one. ma'am. yes.

626
00:41:29.120 --> 00:41:32.896
So this is... exciting news.

627
00:41:32.920 --> 00:41:37.056
You said "suspects".
Who are these suspects?

628
00:41:37.080 --> 00:41:38.376
Oh. yes. sorry.

629
00:41:38.400 --> 00:41:41.376
So far. we've. er. found
fibres that link Dobson. Norris

630
00:41:41.400 --> 00:41:42.936
and both the Acourts.

631
00:41:42.960 --> 00:41:47.256
The same names I gave to a detective
who was in your shoes in 1993.

632
00:41:47.280 --> 00:41:49.320
The names he didn't
even look at.

633
00:41:50.680 --> 00:41:53.816
You know. every few years. I
get called into these meetings

634
00:41:53.840 --> 00:41:56.296
to be told about the new
leads you're pursuing.

635
00:41:56.320 --> 00:41:58.256
but I gave you leads.

636
00:41:58.280 --> 00:42:01.640
I gave you the names 13 years
ago and nothing was done.

637
00:42:04.240 --> 00:42:06.640
Well. that is what
we're here to rectify.

638
00:42:07.680 --> 00:42:10.056
But why does it need
to be rectified?

639
00:42:10.080 --> 00:42:12.320
Why has it taken 13 years?

640
00:42:13.440 --> 00:42:17.256
Building a case is a complex
process. Often. it's...

641
00:42:17.280 --> 00:42:19.136
Ma'am. excuse me. If I may.

642
00:42:19.160 --> 00:42:22.296
Mrs Lawrence. I don't have the
answers to all your questions.

643
00:42:22.320 --> 00:42:24.096
Mistakes were made.

644
00:42:24.120 --> 00:42:26.456
Some of the mistakes. I
can see how they were made.

645
00:42:26.480 --> 00:42:29.536
There were mistaken assumptions
made about the nature of the attack.

646
00:42:29.560 --> 00:42:32.976
I wanna start from scratch
and correct those mistakes.

647
00:42:33.000 --> 00:42:34.856
Other mistakes...

648
00:42:34.880 --> 00:42:37.376
I can't explain them.

649
00:42:37.400 --> 00:42:40.656
There were inexcusable errors
that meant that we failed

650
00:42:40.680 --> 00:42:45.040
in our duty to your
family and to Stephen.

651
00:42:47.920 --> 00:42:50.216
But this is my case now.

652
00:42:50.240 --> 00:42:52.280
and I promise you.

653
00:42:53.560 --> 00:42:55.640
I won't rest until I
arrest your son's killers.

654
00:42:57.200 --> 00:42:58.680
So will you trust me?

655
00:43:00.800 --> 00:43:03.320
Trust has to be
earned. Mr Driscoll.

656
00:43:08.880 --> 00:43:11.536
You started off a bit... Yeah.

657
00:43:11.560 --> 00:43:13.080
But she came round.

658
00:43:15.520 --> 00:43:17.296
We'll see.

659
00:43:17.320 --> 00:43:19.440
Got a lot of ground to
make up. haven't we?

660
00:43:20.600 --> 00:43:24.616
Well. that was...
surprising. Hm.

661
00:43:24.640 --> 00:43:26.936
Bit of a character.
isn't he. DCI Driscoll?

662
00:43:26.960 --> 00:43:29.136
What did you think of him?

663
00:43:29.160 --> 00:43:30.880
We'll see.

664
00:43:32.920 --> 00:43:36.176
♪ My old man said follow the van

665
00:43:36.200 --> 00:43:39.416
♪ And don't
dilly-dally on the way

666
00:43:39.440 --> 00:43:43.656
♪ Off went the cart
With me whole life in it

667
00:43:43.680 --> 00:43:47.376
♪ I followed on With
me old cock linnet

668
00:43:47.400 --> 00:43:50.896
♪ I dillied and dallied
Dallied and dillied

669
00:43:50.920 --> 00:43:53.776
♪ Lost my way And don't
know where to roam

670
00:43:53.800 --> 00:43:58.856
♪ Well. you can't trust a
special Like an old-time copper

671
00:43:58.880 --> 00:44:02.040
♪ When you can't
find Your way home. ♪

672
00:44:04.800 --> 00:44:08.896
"New state-of-the-art
developments in forensic science"?

673
00:44:08.920 --> 00:44:11.616
[SCOFFS]

674
00:44:11.640 --> 00:44:14.576
He told me not to tell
nobody. but it's all here.

675
00:44:14.600 --> 00:44:18.840
"Will you trust me?" He
actually asked me that.

676
00:44:20.160 --> 00:44:23.680
You know what this
is. Same old Met.

677
00:44:26.560 --> 00:44:28.120
[DOOR OPENS]

678
00:44:30.480 --> 00:44:32.520
What?
